</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>364</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-001X</addr>  <route>axt-001X.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date>  <title>Scott space of a dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  Let <tex>(D,  \sqsubseteq )</tex> be a dcpo. The <em>Scott space</em> of <tex>D</tex> is the
  topological space <tex>(D,  \sigma ( D ) )</tex> whose open sets are given by the class
  <tex>\sigma ( D )</tex> of <link href="axt-001Y.xml" type="local" title="Scott open subset of a dcpo">Scott opens</link> of <tex>D</tex>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>365</anchor>  <taxon>Theorem</taxon> <addr>axt-001V</addr>  <route>axt-001V.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  The <link href="axt-001W.xml" type="local" title="Scott locale of a dcpo">Scott locale</link> of any <link href="axt-000J.xml" type="local" title="Scott domain">Scott domain</link> is algebraic.
</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>